@endnode
@node "config" "Help Config"

The Format of the RSAD.cfg file is as follows:

 3                           <-- Number of Attempts users get to get there
                                 pass word right!
 5                           <-- Access to drop to for failure to get the
                                 password right! numbers range from 0-4999
 102                         <-- The linked Section number to the files
                                 areas you want to list as List All Files
 3                           <-- The message section number for your Public
                                 Email to a user
 "Guest Access"              <-- The Name of the Access Level, so the user
                                 knows what there access will be if they
                                 try to hack the door
 "<USER NAME>","<PASSWORD>"  <-- Users Name and Password must be CAPS, Only
                                 add those names for users who are allowed
                                 access

To change any part of the RSAD.cfg file you can easly do this using a
text editor, The second line must be a number between 0-4999. anything over
4999 will result in a note to the sysop stating the door has an error...
this will inform the sysop that the access level inside the RSAD.cfg
file is over the allowed size...
thus effectively making the door useless...

remember 4999 or less means it works, too high and it won't, simple.....
Also trying to HEXEDIT your name into the registration string will disable
the program...

This door also creates a report called `Caught' in the RSAD directory
to inform the Sysop of any illegal activity, i.e. Hacking...
Any user that attempts to use this door without prior permission from the
Sysop, will have there users stats dropped to the number at line 2 of the
config file (Sysop Definable), and is immediately kicked off (TWITTED as
it is known ;-)...
Also if a user is using the door and Loses carrier a report is made to the
sysop that a user Lost Carrier, this file is called RSAD-ErrorLog and is
placed in the RSAD Directory...

I have mine set to drop-kick a user to Guest Access so they can appologise
for trying to hack this door...

using a text editor, you can cut out this example and name it
"RSAD.cfg" or edit and use the sample provided...

                ----------------------CUT-------------------
3
5
102
3
"Guest Access"
"SYSOP NAME",PASSWORD
USER,PASSWORD

                ----------------------CUT-------------------
use Quote marks if names have spaces, see above...

@endnode
@node "use" "Using the Door"

General menu functions:

1> Sysop Information
   This displays the same infomation as when the BBS is Idle...

2> List All Files On The System
   This function accesses a linked files section and displays every
   file that you want linked into this list...
   Area Definable by the sysop...

3> Do a RAW Download
   This lets the user of the door perform a d/l of any files on HD
   without haveing to go into a files area...

4> Open a CLI
   Open MAXsBBS's internal Cli...

5> Randy's Remote User Editor
   Allows you to Edit any of the current users except those with sysop
   access (10000) ie YOUR account...
   For more information on @{" Using The Remote User Editor " link "RUE" 0}

6> Randy's Remote File Editor
   Allow you to Edit the info of any file online, New Files can also
   be edited...
   For more information on @{" Using The Remote File Editor " link "RFE" 0}

7> Leave a Message to a User
   Self explainatory...

8> List of Hacking Attempts
   Lists all those users who tryed to gain access to this door...
   and failed ;)

9> Delete HACKERS list
   This delete's the list of those who failed to get passed the programs
   defences :)...

0> View Randy's User Editor Logfile...

E> View RSAD Error Logfile...

Q> Return to the BBS
   Err Well umm... Quit's the door...

A> About
   Some information on the program Version etc...

R> Redraw Menu
   If at anytime the menu get's mangled, this function resets it to
   normal...

@endnode
@node "install" "Installing as a MAX's Door"

To install as a Door under MAX's BBS do the following:

1, Create a Directory in your Doors: path called RSAD
2, Copy all files in the archive to the RSAD directory
3, In the MAX'sBBS Sections config, link all file areas to 102
4, Edit Config File to suit your system
5, Run as a MAXsBBS Door using the example below

example of the menu function:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

  key:  Function:  Extra  Lo acc:  Hi acc   Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
   A     34        0      10000    10000    Doors:RSAD/RSAD

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALLING the FAKE, Make users think they have accessed the door :-D

*** Note: Use the same Key!! ***
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

  key:  Function:  Extra  Lo acc:  Hi acc   Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
   A     34        0      10       10000    Doors:RSAD/FakeRSAD

---------------------------------------------------------------------------


@endnode
@node "hist" "The Programs History"

               Project Started on 10-Sep-1995 My Birthday


1.0, 10-Sep-95, never released, fulla bugs, test period

1.2, 25-Sep-95, First beta release, fixed 2 severe bug's which caused this
                door to lock up the system on exiting...

1.3 <-> 1.9,    never Released, due to severe bug...

2.0, 02-Nov-95, Severe Bug found and removed...

2.1, 17-Nov-95, Bug fix and an Overhaul of the frontend...
                still needs work...
                Also added some internal ANSI code for the information
                screen...

2.1a 18-Nov-95, Included ANSI menu and sysop info files into code...
                also fixed a small bug in the Clear Text code...
                Placed a small routine in, just in case hackers attempt to
                change the access codes file...

2.2, 08-Dec-95, Upgraded the ANSI's and gave it a nicer front end...
                miner bug fix after getting a friend to test the hacker
                trap...
                descovered he could alter the config file...
                bug found and removed...

2.2a 08-Dec-95, Same day service :) Bug fix, added tamper proof code...
                for testing registration code purposes...
                left it in for program defences...
                Finally Created this AmigaGuige Document...

2.21 02-Jan-96, ** Official Release **
                Added code supplied by Randy Quick into the program...
                any bugs can be reported to me at anyone of my e-mail
                addresses...

2.22 05-Jan-96, ** Update/Bug Fix **
                Fixed a major bug in the code that caused the BBS to lockup
                when a user lost carrier...
                Thank's to Randy Quick for pointing this error out to me...

3.00 03-Mar-96, ** Power Features Version **
                Added Randy Quick's Remote User and File Editors into the
                Program... Thank's Randy, this was a Joint Effort...

3.01 15-Mar-96  ** Bug Fix **
                Found a bug in the code that locked the system up for 5 secs
                during a LostCarrier... Fixed...
                also change the name to RSAD " Remote Sysop Access Door "

