@node "rfe" "Useing The Remote File Editor"

Direct Insert of Randy Quick's Docs...

Randy's Remote File Editor allows editing from remote of all file
attributes (including deletion) that can be edited -

NOTE:-  These can not be changed by the Editor:

The filename.
The file size.
The date this file was Upload/Added to the BBS.

The Attributes that can be Edited Include:

              Uploader's name               Section number
              Uploader's alias              Deleted status
              File description              Locked status
              Number of downloads           New/public status


           @{" V E R Y    I M P O R T A N T    R E A D    B E L O W "}

In this archive is a small programme called RFETest - *MAKE SURE* that the
line "run BBS:RFETest" (or wherever you put it) is inserted in your
startup-sequence somewhere before you start MAX'sBBS. It creates a small
file called Ram:RFEDataFile that Randy's Remote File Editor needs to work
correctly. - If this file is not found the program reports an error then
exits back to the BBS...

For those who already have this file and use Randy's RFE program please
continue using the one you have...

                               ****************

When Randy's Remote File Editor is entered it will ask you if you want to
process <N>ew files  or <E>nter file name.

If you select <N>ew files, it will find all new files on the system and
present them one at a time for editing.

If you select <E> it will ask you for the file name (it will search on the
first characters of the name) and display the current settings of the above
attributes for the first filename that matches (no further searching is done)

It will then prompt you for which to change.  Having changed that one, it
will re-prompt, so you can change as many of the attributes as you care to
in one sitting.  Note that, if you want to clear any of the first three,
(the uploader, alias or description) press <Del> and then <Return> (a blank
space doesn't work - it will just retain the current value).

When finished, select <0> and it will ask if you wish to save the changes.

Select <S> to save or press the "Any" key to quit.



@endnode
